<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Pitt-Des Moines Inc. said it will establish
an employee stock ownership plan.
   The company will acquire at fair market value and
contribute to the ESOP about 57,000 shares of its common
stock from certain Jackson family charitable trusts. The
family of chairman emeritus William R. Jackson holds a total
of 1,173,815 shares out of 2,400,000 shares outstanding.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it has entered into agreements with
certain members of the Jackson family providing for the
future purchase from their estates of about 255,000 shares.
Those shares represent a portion of their current share
ownership.
   The steel fabricator said the steps were taken to address
what will happen to shares owned by the Jacksons upon their
death.
</TEXT>
